The documents provided contain information that supports the statement "The capital of Southern Nigeria Protectorate is Lagos." Specifically, multiple sources indicate that Lagos became the capital of the Southern Nigeria Protectorate in February 1906 and continued to serve as the capital when the Colony and Protectorate of Southern Nigeria was amalgamated with Northern Nigeria into the single Colony and Protectorate of Nigeria on January 1, 1914.

mistral.reason: Lagos was the capital of the Colony and Protectorate of Nigeria, not just the Southern Nigeria Protectorate. The incorrect statement implies that Calabar, not Lagos, was the capital of the Southern Nigeria Protectorate, which was part of the Colony and Protectorate of Nigeria from 1906 to 1914, with Lagos as its capital.
